@startuml
title ModBusX – Deployment (Desktop)

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam nodeBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam artifactBackgroundColor #FFF2CC
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #D5E8D4
skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor #E8F4FD
  BackgroundColor<<production>> #D5E8D4
  BackgroundColor<<enterprise>> #FFE4B5
  BackgroundColor<<cloud>> #E0F6FF
}
skinparam artifact {
  BackgroundColor #FFF2CC
  BackgroundColor<<production>> #D5E8D4
  BackgroundColor<<enterprise>> #FFE4B5
  BackgroundColor<<cloud>> #E0F6FF
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #D5E8D4
  BackgroundColor<<enterprise>> #FFE4B5
  BackgroundColor<<cloud>> #E0F6FF
}

node "User Desktop" <<production>> as Desktop {
  artifact "ModBusX App" <<production>> as App {
    [PyQt5 UI]
    [AsyncModbusServer]
    [PyModbus]
  }
  database "User Data" <<production>> as UserData {
    [~/.modbusx/logs]
    [settings.json]
  }
}

cloud "Modbus Network" as Net {
  node "Modbus Master (TCP)" as MasterTCP
  node "Serial Master (RTU/ASCII)" as MasterSER
}

Desktop -down-> Net : TCP 502
Desktop -down-> MasterSER : Serial (COM/tty)

' Development Environment
DevApp --> DevConfig : reads/writes
DevApp --> DevTools : uses
DevApp ..> ModbusNet : TCP/502, RTU/Serial

' Production Desktop
ProdApp --> ProdData : stores configs
ProdApp --> ProdDeps : uses
ProdApp ..> ModbusNet : ModBus TCP/RTU

' Enterprise Environment
ServerApp --> EntDB : stores data
ServerApp ..> ModbusNet : proxy connections
EntClients --> ServerApp : HTTPS/REST API
ServerApp --> Container : deployed in

' Cloud Environment
ClientApp --> Gateway : HTTPS/API calls
Gateway --> Microservices : routes requests
Microservices --> CloudDB : data persistence
Microservices ..> ModbusNet : secure tunnels
Monitoring --> Microservices : monitors health

' Cross-environment data flow
DevApp -.-> ProdApp : deployment pipeline
ProdApp -.-> EntServer : configuration export
EntServer -.-> CloudInfra : cloud migration

' ========== NETWORK PROTOCOLS ==========
note top of ModbusNet
**ModBus Protocol Support:**
• TCP/IP Server (Port 502)
• RTU Serial Server (COM ports)
• ASCII Serial Server (COM ports)
• PyModbus 3.x Compatible
• Exclusive COM port access
• PLC & Protocol addressing modes
end note

note top of EntServer
**Enterprise Features:**
• Multi-user access
• Role-based permissions
• Centralized configuration
• Historical data logging
• RESTful API
end note

note top of CloudInfra
**Cloud Benefits:**
• Auto-scaling
• High availability
• Global deployment
• Managed services
• Monitoring & alerting
end note

' ========== DEPLOYMENT ENVIRONMENTS ==========

package "Deployment Environments" {
    rectangle "Development" #E8F4FD {
        [Local development]
        [Unit testing]
        [Integration testing]
        [Diagram generation]
    }
    
    rectangle "Staging" #FFF2CC {
        [User acceptance testing]
        [Performance testing]
        [Security testing]
        [Documentation review]
    }
    
    rectangle "Production" #D5E8D4 {
        [Desktop deployment]
        [Enterprise deployment]
        [Cloud deployment]
        [Monitoring & support]
    }
}

' ========== SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS ==========
note as SecurityNote
**Security Considerations:**
• ModBus protocol security (limited)
• VPN tunnels for remote access
• Certificate-based authentication
• Network segmentation
• Audit logging
• Role-based access control
• Encrypted configuration storage
end note

SecurityNote .. ModbusNet

' ========== SCALABILITY NOTES ==========
note as ScalabilityNote
**Scalability Patterns:**
• Horizontal scaling (microservices)
• Connection pooling
• Caching strategies
• Async operations
• Load balancing
• Database sharding
• Event-driven architecture
end note

ScalabilityNote .. CloudInfra

@enduml
